Xavier-Luc Duval Named Mauritius Finance & Economy Minister

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-08-06T16:37:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-06/xavier-luc-duval-named-mauritius-finance-economy-minister-1-.html
Xavier-Luc Duval has been named
finance and economic development minister for Mauritius, the
state-owned Broadcasting Corp TV channel said today.  Duval is the leader of the Parti Mauricien Social
Democrate, which is part of the Labor Party-led ruling alliance.
Duval, 53, has held four ministerial posts since 1995, including
the tourism and industrial portfolios. He holds a degree in
economics from Leeds University in the U.K. and is a Fellow of
the Institute of Chartered Accountants in  England  and Wales.  Duvalâ€™s nomination is part of a cabinet reshuffle announced
today following the resignation of six ministers, including
former Finance Minister Pravind Jugnauth on July 26.  To contact the reporter on this story:
